"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Since making its initial $250-million Bitcoin investment in August 2020, MicroStrategy has gone on to purchase billions of dollars in Bitcoin in separate buys using the companyâ€™s cash on hand in addition to [sales of convertible senior notes](https://cointelegraph.com/news/microstrategy-raising-600m-no-900m-to-buy-more-bitcoin) in private offerings to institutional buyers. Though there are cases in which the [business intelligence firm bought the dip](https://cointelegraph.com/news/microstrategy-buys-the-dip-acquires-10m-in-bitcoin), some buys followed the price surges in early 2021 when the BTC price was more than $50,000.\\n\\n***Related: [MicroStrategy pledges to buy more BTC despite paper loss on its holdings of $424.8M in Q2](https://cointelegraph.com/news/microstrategy-pledges-to-buy-more-btc-despite-paper-loss-on-its-holdings-of-424-8m-in-q2)***\\n\\nAccording to data from [Cointelegraph Markets Pro](https://pro.cointelegraph.com/?via=news), the price of Bitcoin is $48,684 at the time of publication, having fallen more than 25% in the last 30 days. The crypto asset has been hovering near $50,000 since [dipping to the $42,000s](https://cointelegraph.com/news/bitcoin-rebounds-on-wall-street-open-as-exchange-btc-reserves-plunge-after-42k-dip) on Friday.\",\"timestamp\":1639128663,\"title\":\"Assistant Foreign Minister Wu Jianghao said the white\"},\"digest\":\"GvbdPdPyWzsAXKqpXcmqVLk8q-IRA8CkU9mZK9i6fIE\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x0673063253C4B41B39848D7Dd4d9dcF9dDCfE324\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"lgZ0YvfcN_2Me-5-LxUGiWt_1V5irqlgSxTCJ5DT6o8\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"yseyY6yg3xDgIClSZcfVEWo4XpBj1VX05QIjEhD5g-8\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"I7ZbHe4UYMAFUrhqVKl5eXzJEIW8BoXtHOHdskQfStEa4HDaUM_xajbOklb0XWWRft_I941x_MONMY-uJG8mNA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xa5be4829513ed9f339e7e83f05de0e10d927591f10c95e3b1959a99b4bb2427b5e4d9636d218cc64611